==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swimmeret
<hw>Swim"mer*et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of a series of flat, fringed, and usually bilobed, appendages,
of which several pairs occur on the abdominal somites of many
crustaceans. They are used as fins in swimming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swimming</ent>⟦br⟧
